# aws-http-auth

[![PyPI - Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/aws-http-auth.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/aws-http-auth)
[![PyPI - Python Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/aws-http-auth.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/aws-http-auth)
[![pre-commit.ci status](https://results.pre-commit.ci/badge/github/FlavioAmurrioCS/aws-http-auth/main.svg)](https://results.pre-commit.ci/latest/github/FlavioAmurrioCS/aws-http-auth/main)

Lightweight AWS SigV4 signing and HTTP authentication for httpx, requests, and raw HTTP clientsâ€”without the weight of boto3.

-----

## Features

- ðŸš€ **Lightweight**: No heavy dependencies like boto3â€”just pure AWS SigV4 signing
- ðŸ”— **Universal**: Works with `requests`, `httpx`, and any HTTP client that supports auth handlers
- ðŸ”‘ **Flexible credentials**: Load from AWS credentials file, environment variables, or provide directly
- ðŸŽ¯ **Zero config**: Automatically detects AWS regions and services from URLs
- ðŸŒ **Pyodide compatible**: Works in browser environments with WebAssembly
- ðŸ“¦ **Type safe**: Full type hints for better development experience

